CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 20, 1970, pg. 16, reads: "Male Group - The Pittsburgh Chapter of Tots and Teens is a husband and wife organization.  Here is the male contingent.  Seated from left: Carl Southers, Joseph Barrow, Alfred Hunt, James Armstrong, Alfred Hopson, James Lightfoot and Wilmer Barnes.  Standing: Melvin Smith, Lewis Hubert Smith, Jesse Bolden, Thomas Hull, Charles Franklin, Asby Dunning, Robert Russell, Leo Woods, Lawrence Moncrief and Robert Mahaffey. - Harris photos."
TitMainTitle: Members of Tots and Teens, seated from left: Carl Southers, Joseph Barrow, Alfred Hunt, James Armstrong, Alfred Hopson, James Lightfoot and Wilmer Barnes; standing: Melvin Smith, Lewis Hubert Smith, Jesse Bolden, Thomas Hull, Charles Franklin, Asby Dunning, Robert Russell, Leo Woods, Lawrence Moncrief, and Robert Mahaffey posed in Roosevelt Hotel
